# Binaries
/mcp-midi-controller
/aum-test
/usb-probe
/widi-probe
/auv3-probe
/dist/
*.exe

# Go
/vendor/

# Web UI (signalwave). node_modules and the docs bundle staged by the Vite
# prebuild step are generated; the built SPA in internal/webui/dist is committed
# (consumed by go:embed) so the Go binary builds without Node.
/web/node_modules/
/web/public/docs/
/web/*.tsbuildinfo

# Editor / OS
*.swp
.DS_Store

# Private, installation-specific docs (rig snapshots, real names/IPs/scenes).
# The repo is public; keep anything specific to one setup out of git.
/docs/private/
*.local.md

# Private docs bundled into local webapp builds by web/scripts/copy-docs.mjs.
# The committed dist must never contain them.
/internal/webui/dist/docs/private/
/internal/webui/dist/docs/manifest.private.json

# The public/private + reverse-engineering policy rule. Kept out of the public
# repo "just in case" so the RE strategy notes stay private.
/.cursor/rules/public-vs-private.mdc

# graphify knowledge graph (regenerable, rebuilt by the post-commit hook)
graphify-out/

# Local-only AUM diagnostics: one-off investigation tools that read real,
# machine-specific session files from the config dir. Not part of the build or
# the committed test suite — kept local so they don't pollute the public tree.
/cmd/_scratch_*/
/internal/aum/diag_test.go
